

=== Background to chi analysis

Chi analysis, or stem:[/chi] analysis, is a means of normalizing channel gradient for either drainage area or discharge.

Chi analysis is a method for examining channel profiles.
If you are familiar with chi analysis, you can skip ahead to the section <<Get and compile the chi analysis tools>>.
This section covers the background to the method, and why it is useful.

